@model dynamic

@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Features - Hadouken";
}

@section Scripts {
    <script type="text/javascript" src="~/Scripts/Features.Index/holder.js"></script>
}

<div id="feature-carousel" class="carousel slide" data-ride="carousel">
    <ol class="carousel-indicators">
        <li data-target="#feature-carousel" data-slide-to="0" class="active"></li>
        <li data-target="#feature-carousel" data-slide-to="1"></li>
        <li data-target="#feature-carousel" data-slide-to="2"></li>
    </ol>

    <div class="carousel-inner">
        <div class="item active">
            <img src="@Url.Content("~/content/features/setup.png")" alt="..." />
        </div>

        <div class="item">
            <img src="@Url.Content("~/content/features/plugins.png")" alt="..." />
        </div>

        <div class="item">
            <img src="@Url.Content("~/content/features/torrentconfig.png")" alt="..." />
        </div>
    </div>

    <a class="left carousel-control" href="#feature-carousel" data-slide="prev">
        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-left"></span>
    </a>
    <a class="right carousel-control" href="#feature-carousel" data-slide="next">
        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-right"></span>
    </a>
</div>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-lg-12">
        <h3>Friendly interface</h3>
        
        <p>The first time you open up the web interface, we will guide you through the configuring process. The wizard is completely optional (like most of Hadoukens configuration) and is there purely to get you going quickly.</p>
        
        <p>We try to have sensible defaults everywhere and keep mandatory settings to a minimum. The only configuration we want you to to is the one that provides value, like telling Hadouken to subscribe to a specific RSS feed, or
        setting up watched folders.</p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-lg-12">
        <h3>Plugins</h3>

        <p>The plugin support in Hadouken is awesome for end users and developers alike. From the web interface it is super easy to upload new plugins or upgrade existing ones.</p>

        <p>For developers, the plugin API will provide you with everything you need to get going. We dogfood the API daily, and most of the core functionality in Hadouken is actually a plugin. Therefore you can rely on the API being stable and well-proven.</p>
    </div>
</div>